  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: physical faults gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CPB pump operates in vivo during extended perfusion procedures lasting up to 6–8 hours, in a clinical environment subject to mechanical wear of the impeller bearing, transient electrical supply fluctuations at the motor drive, and occasional partial occlusion of inlet tubing. These operational realities impose fault states on the physical hardware that differ materially from nominal design-point operation.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "conformsToProfile_cou": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
