      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model must be justified by literature precedent for centrifugal blood pump CFD.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected per FDA-sponsored round-robin benchmark findings. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied as per published CPB CFD practice. Model form represents steady-state nominal pump geometry; no degraded or fault-state model form (e.g., eccentric impeller orbit from worn bearing) is included in the model formulation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties must be derived from measured data or published standards with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate from calibrated ultrasonic flowmeter (±1.5%). Rotational speed from optical tachometer (±5 RPM). Blood viscosity from Carreau-Yasuda fit to rheometry data (R² = 0.997). Pump geometry from CMM measurement of nominal hardware. Inputs characterize nominal operating state; degraded-hardware inputs (e.g., increased bearing clearance, reduced motor torque under voltage sag) are not represented."
